{"action": "input", "code": "def find_boundaries(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> Tuple[int, int, int, int]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given an input grid, this function returns the upper, lower, left and right boundaries of the non-black pixels.\n    \n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid\n    \n    Returns:\n    A tuple of four integers representing the upper, lower, left and right boundaries of the non-black pixels.\n    \"\"\"\n    non_black_pixels = np.where(input_grid != black)\n    upper, left = np.min(non_black_pixels, axis=1)\n    lower, right = np.max(non_black_pixels, axis=1)\n    return (upper, lower, left, right)\ndef main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    upper, lower, left, right = find_boundaries(input_grid)\n    output_grid = turn_pixels_red(upper, lower, left, right, input_grid)\n    return output_grid\ndef turn_pixels_red(upper: int, lower: int, left: int, right: int, input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given an input grid and the upper, lower, left and right boundaries of the non-black pixels, this function turns all non-black pixels in this range into red.\n    \n    Args:\n    upper: An integer representing the upper boundary of the non-black pixels.\n    lower: An integer representing the lower boundary of the non-black pixels.\n    left: An integer representing the left boundary of the non-black pixels.\n    right: An integer representing the right boundary of the non-black pixels.\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid\n    \n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the output grid with all non-black pixels in the given range turned into red.\n    \"\"\"\n    output_grid = input_grid.copy()\n    output_grid[upper:lower + 1, left:right + 1][output_grid[upper:lower + 1, left:right + 1] != black] = red\n    return output_grid", "user_code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    upper, lower, left, right = `Find the upper, lower, left, right boundaries of the 